<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/3244</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-21T18:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.40 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5355. Your 4110,<note n="2" xml:id="d650fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_520">p.
                                    520</ref>.</note> December 1, 7 p. m. and 4144,<note n="3" xml:id="d650fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_521">p.
                                    521</ref>.</note> December 7, 6 p. m. In support of the original
                                request contained in your 4048,<note n="2" xml:id="d650fn3">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_520">p.
                                    520</ref>.</note> November 16, 3 p. m., which was answered by
                                Foreign Office in the sense of my 5272 [5271?],<note n="3" xml:id="d650fn4">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_521">p.
                                    521</ref>.</note> December 5, 5 p. m., renewed representations
                                based on your above instructions were presented. Foreign Office
                                replies in note received to-day that the concession made upon my
                                request and contained in my note quoted in my 5076,<note n="4" xml:id="d650fn5">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_519">p.
                                    519</ref>.</note> October 26, was intended to operate in
                                substitution for previous arrangements and that in these
                                circumstances it regrets its inability to accede to the request
                                based on your 4110, December 1, 7 p. m., and 4144, December 7, 6 p.
                                    m.<note n="5" xml:id="d650fn6">According to telegram No. 406,
                                    December 23, from the Minister in Denmark, arrangements were
                                    finally completed for the release of the detained tobacco in
                                    compliance with existing regulations. (File No.
                                    763.72112/3248.)</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>